  "instructions": [
    "Slice the green peppers, onions, and shallots into thin strips.",
    "Heat a large skillet with vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the sliced ingredients and stir-fry for about 5 minutes until they start to soften.",
    "Add garlic and oyster sauce to the skillet. Stir well to incorporate all the flavors.",
    "Mix in tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, and water. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Simmer for an additional 2-3 minutes until the mixture thickens slightly.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or over rice."
